title: South Korea Three Month Interbank Rate
description: South Korea Three Month Interbank Rate was at 3.96 percent on Monday November 7. Interbank Rate in South Korea averaged 2.68 percent from 2004 until 2022, reaching an all time high of 6.14 percent in October of 2008 and a record low of 0.57 percent in August of 2020. In South Korea, the interbank rate is the rate of interest charged on short-term loans made between banks. This page provides - South Korea Overnight Interbank Rate - actual values, historical data, forecast, chart, statistics, economic calendar and news.
author: The Bank of Korea
